-- China Vice President Xi Urges Closer Economic Ties With U.S., Xinhua Says
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2010-10-13T09:21:58Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-13/china-vice-president-xi-urges-closer-economic-ties-with-u-s-xinhua-says.html
Chinese Vice President Xi Jinping
called for closer financial, economic and trade cooperation with
the U.S., Xinhua News Agency reported.  The Chinese leader made the comments at a meeting with U.S.
Senator Max Baucus in Beijing today, Xinhua said.  Xi urged the U.S. to increase high-tech exports to China,
the news agency said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bloomberg News at 
 gturk2@bloomberg.net  